# Codex Writer Findings — PublicMenu Chain: publicmenu-260330-161543-9b4e

## Findings
1. [P1] Fix 1 / CV-05-v2 — `renderBucketOrders()` still renders `<Rating>` rows for every served item as soon as the bucket opens (`CartView.jsx:513-584`), and there is no `isRatingMode` state near the other `useState` declarations (`CartView.jsx:93-117`). The default expanded view therefore still shows empty star widgets instead of right-aligned `Оценить` / `⭐N` status text. FIX: add `isRatingMode` state and split served rendering into view mode text vs rating mode stars, with `⭐{rating}` for rated items and `review.rate_action` for unrated ones.
2. [P1] Fix 2 / CV-05-chip — The served-bucket chip is still a static orange `Оценить` button in both served paths (`CartView.jsx:810-817`, `CartView.jsx:923-929`). It does not show `Оценить (N)`, never switches to `Готово`, uses `e.stopPropagation()`, and there is no unrated counter, rating-mode micro-label, or scroll-to-first-unrated behavior. FIX: compute `unratedServedCount`, make chip tap expand + enable rating mode, swap label to `Готово` while active, add `Режим оценки`, and scroll the first unrated row into view.
3. [P2] Fix 3 / CV-37 — The bonus hint remains an amber banner inside expanded served content in both render branches (`CartView.jsx:829-834`, `CartView.jsx:941-945`). The required muted subline below the served header button is missing. FIX: remove the in-content amber banner and render the `За отзыв можно получить +N баллов` subline directly under the served header, outside the `expandedStatuses.served` block.
4. [P1] Fix 4 / CV-39 — Rating autosave still hard-locks items after the first selection: `onChange` returns early on `draftRating > 0 || hasReview` and the `Rating` stays `readonly` under the same condition (`CartView.jsx:559-575`). Save feedback is also incomplete: the UI only shows a spinner or bare checkmark (`CartView.jsx:576-580`), so there is no `Сохраняем…` / `Сохранено` / `Ошибка. Повторить` state mapping, and a truthy `'error'` value would currently render as "saving". FIX: only block while `ratingSavingByItemId[item.itemId] === true`, keep immediate `handleRateDish`, and branch the status text for saving, saved, and error.
5. [P2] Fix 5 / CV-36 — The all-rated state is only partially implemented. The served chip renders plain `Оценено` without the required `✓` prefix and `review.all_rated_chip` copy (`CartView.jsx:811-813`, `CartView.jsx:923-924`), and there is no logic that exits rating mode once the last unrated item is saved. FIX: render the read-only `✓ Оценено` indicator and add auto-exit when `allServedRated` becomes true.
6. [P2] Fix 6 / CV-38 — The post-rating email flow is still inline inside the served bucket (`CartView.jsx:835-889`, `CartView.jsx:947-1000`). There is no `showPostRatingEmailSheet` state, no `Готово`-triggered bottom sheet, and the email prompt still appears before explicit completion. FIX: delete the inline green nudge block, add a dedicated post-rating sheet triggered from `Готово`, and reuse the existing email submit logic there.
7. [P2] Fix 7 / CV-40 — Re-entry is not implemented. Rated items use `value={draftRating}` only (`CartView.jsx:555-559`), so saved review values are not prefilled from existing reviews, and `readonly={draftRating > 0 || hasReview || ...}` prevents editing after re-entry (`CartView.jsx:574`). FIX: feed `Rating` from the draft-or-existing review value and allow edits whenever the row is not actively saving.
8. [P2] Fix 8 / CV-42 — The star row still uses `className="flex items-center gap-2 pl-2 py-1"` (`CartView.jsx:557`) rather than `min-h-[44px]`, so the required 44px mobile tap target has not been applied. FIX: change the row container to `min-h-[44px]` and keep `size="md"` on the `Rating` control.
9. [P3] Fix 9 / PM-164 — The guest-name edit button still has `min-h-[44px]` (`CartView.jsx:635-640`), so the extra vertical gap under the guest line remains. FIX: change only that button to `min-h-[32px]`.
10. [P3] Fix 10 / PM-165 — The bucket items container still includes `pt-1` in `className="space-y-1 mt-1 pt-1"` (`CartView.jsx:543`), so the extra gap between a bucket header and its first dish is still present. FIX: remove `pt-1` and keep `space-y-1 mt-1`.

## Summary
Total: 10 findings (0 P0, 3 P1, 5 P2, 2 P3)

